Package com.netcracker.tc.types.standard Description

Standard types implementation.

Standard types:

  • boolean (yes/no) BoolType

    Use Param.description() to set checkbox text in editor widget.

    Param.defValue() can be "true" or "false" (default).

    This type is inferred for boolean params and fields.

  • enumeration (one value from fixed set of options) EnumType

    This type is inferred for fields and params of some Enum type

    Override Enum.toString() to change display

    Param.defValue() can be name of enum value.

  • integer number IntType

    Use Int.min() and Int.max() to set bounds.

    Type is inferred for fields and params of int or Integer type.

  • string StringType

    Use Str annotation to make parameter required (non-empty), set max length or regexp pattern.

  • output reference RefType

    Inferred for any field or parameter with Ref annotation.

    References outputs of previous scenarios in current test case with same type, as set in Ref.value().
